Assignement Title: Visual Prompt Studio Phase 1.1 
Prompt: Create a poster of a science fiction blockbuster that feautres the landscape of a world that shows the difference between kids that enjoy playing outside and kids that spend their time on tablets at home in the Dallas city. The houses and buildings should be big with vertical lines to show the strength in communicating the difference between the scenarios. The texture of the city should be very open minded and outgoing, with pstel colors showing happiness, as the children inside on taqblets should show a texture of dark and empty minded, as in no type of imagination just straight showing focus on the tablet and not on what's going on outside in the world. There should aslo be contrast between the colors from the outside and inside to communicate the different type of ways the kids see the world. 
Vocabulary Breakdown: Volume- refers to the three-dimensional quality of an object, meaning it has height, width, and depth. It makes the object look solid, and occupy space. Lines- Are a continuous mark made by a moving point that has length and direction. It is used to define shapes, create outlines and guide the audience/viewer's eyes through thr artwork itself. Shape- A two dimensional area that has height and width and is closed by lines, colors or textures. Artists use shapes to create patterns, organie ideas and represent objects. Texture- The surface quality of an object, how it feels or how it may seem to feel. Contrast- The principle of art that uses noticeable differences, such as color, value, texture, size to create visual interest.
